13. At about 1hr ten min, Donna spoke adamantly about how she feels her lawsuit was not just for her, but for ALL the candidates removed illegally. The People should be the ones who decide who wins an election! The delegates were also silenced as part of the "sham political process". Both main parties are involved in the Marxist agenda.

14. One of the reasons Donna chose Mellissa as a running mate is that she is very strong-willed. Donna says a governor should not have a lieutenant who just agrees and supports her every move. If Carone disagrees, Donna knows she can count on her to say so, with intelligence and integrity. This helps ensure that the right decisions are made for the People.

15. Donna found out about Ryan Kelley's statement in support of the Dixon/Hernandez ticket while doing the video and read it aloud, somewhere about the 1hr 40min mark. Her immediate reaction to it was, "How about the Republican crime family? 'Cause there's a whole bunch of them in there involved in this." They both find his statement to be disingenuous.

16. At almost 2hrs in, Mellissa says, "What is wrong with you?!" I totally agree. She is reacting to the idea that people KNOW Dixon was "installed" onto the ballot, but are fighting to support her name anyway. This is a blind fight for the cabal, not based on common sense, in my mind. Those are Karen the Riveter's words, but it seems Mellissa agrees with the sentiment.

Donna goes on to remind everyone who is in charge. We are to follow God, not man, as we will be held accountable to God alone in the end. We should be brave, like Lot, who left his home behind when it could not be saved, to follow God's instruction. We may have to leave a political party to follow God. That should not be a hard choice, if that is what we believe is true and necessary.

"But there will be a split!" "God can move mountains!", Donna said. Oh, ye of little faith! I do not doubt the power of God; I trust in His ability to design that which He wishes. I can only decide what my decision is based on my faith in Him, and then let go and let God make the way.

17. At around 2hrs ten min, they mention Stand Up MI, which went from an org to an LLC (to hide financials?). They suggest we should look closer--not at the good Patriots following, but at the origins and leadership of SUMI. There is a rumor (so I won't share it) about the origin, which is NOT good. But Melissa added that they were a first to send her a "cease and desist". ü§î When such people try so hard, which so much funding, to send you in a certain direction which doesn't make sense, it should give us spidey sense tingles and pause to look closer before we believe and obey.

Lastly, from me: back at #16, I started off on my own tangent based on what Donna started on there. I'd like to go back to it.

I would like to challenge you all to make a list of your priorities--who or what is most important to you? If you do this at Thanksgiving time, this should be easy, so maybe think of it that way.

Hopefully God is first, probably followed by family, maybe country.

Where on that list is your party affiliation?

I'm guessing you probably don't think to put that on your "I'm thankful for" list, or high on your priorities list. I know I don't!

Now, I want you to think about how you should cast your ballot. Shouldn't you do so with YOUR priorities in mind?

Would you cast your ballot for someone you don't believe in? Would you cast your ballot for the "lesser of two evils"? Would you cast your ballot because Trump "endorsed" them?

Did you take a shot when Trump said it was a good thing to do?
